Tidying data and adding on win percentage

library(Lahman)
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)
data("Teams")
data("Salaries")
teams <- as.data.table(Teams)
salaries <- as.data.table(Salaries)
teams[, WinPercent := W / (W + L)]
salaries[, `:=`(lgID = as.character(lgID), teamID = as.character(teamID), salary1M = salary / 1e6)]
payroll <- salaries[, .(payroll = sum(salary1M)), by = .(teamID, yearID)]
teamPayroll <- merge(teams, payroll, by = c("teamID", "yearID"))
write.csv(teamPayroll, file = "teamPayroll.csv")

Scatter plot of team payroll and win precentage

ggplot(teamPayroll, aes(x = payroll, y = WinPercent)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue") +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x, se = FALSE, color = "red") +
  labs(
    x = "Team Payroll (in millions USD)",
    y = "Win Percentage",
    title = "Relationship Between Team Payroll and Win Percentage in MLB",
    subtitle = "Linear Regression Analysis",
    caption = "Data source: Lahman Baseball Database"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman"),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 15, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 12, hjust = 0.5),
    plot.caption = element_text(size = 12, hjust = 0.5),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12)
  )

Scatter plots for 5 year intervals

intervals <- seq(1985, 2015, by = 5)
for (interval in intervals) {
  data_interval <- teamPayroll[yearID >= interval & yearID <= (interval + 5)]
  linear_model <- lm(WinPercent ~ payroll, data = data_interval)
  plot <- ggplot(data_interval, aes(x = payroll, y = WinPercent)) +
    geom_point(color = "blue") +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x, se = FALSE, color = "red") +
    labs(
      x = "Team Payroll (in millions USD)",
      y = "Win Percentage",
      title = paste("5-Year Interval ", interval, " - Linear Regression Analysis", sep = ""),
      subtitle = "Effect of Payroll on Performance",
      caption = "Data source: Lahman Baseball Database"
    ) +
    theme_minimal()
  print(plot)
}

Model #2: 5 year interval regression models

for (interval in intervals) {
  data_interval <- teamPayroll[yearID >= interval & yearID <= (interval + 5)]
  linear_model <- lm(WinPercent ~ payroll, data = data_interval)
  test_results <- summary(linear_model)
  cat("5-Year Interval:", interval, "-", interval + 5, "\n")
  cat("Regression Results:\n")
  print(test_results)
  cat("\n")
}

Residual plots for 5 year intervals

create_residual_plot <- function(data, interval) {
  linear_model <- lm(WinPercent ~ payroll, data = data)
  plot(linear_model, which = 1, main = paste("Residual Plot for", interval, "-", interval + 5))
}


for (interval in intervals) {
  data_interval <- teamPayroll[yearID >= interval & yearID <= (interval + 5)]
  create_residual_plot(data_interval, interval)
}
